rComments: This class used to be an easy A, but this semester everything changed. The exams are actually hard, you really should go to class, and he grades BOGUS on the quizzes. Don't take this class because you heard it was easy! But if you're interested in the subject, go for it. He reads off lecture slides and can't really answer questions. Questionable.

really nice guy. Pretty laid back and easy to understand. His tests are much easier than Cronan's (who teaches the first half of the class). Reading over the notes helps alot for exams. Book use isnt necessary but can help if you space out in class or need a review of what was said in class

He's not too easy, but not too hard either.  For the most part he reads from his notes so it's pretty easy to follow his lectures.  I suggest reviewing the lecture slides and looking in the book to get a full understanding of the figures he uses when studying for his exams.
Great guy. He is really helpful, go to office hours.

Basically reads off the slides in the powerpoint.  Go to lecture, take some notes and stay awake.  He teaches this course the second half of the semester and does not usually teach the course (Off semester this year).
I didnt go one day to lecture at all and got an A, i just saw the prof last day of class when i went to pick my exam up. Take IT
his lecture was very clear and funny as other ppl already mentioned and exams were pretty fair if you go over the lecture notes.
his lecture was very clear and funny as other ppl already mentioned and exams were pretty fair if you go over the lecture notes.

Prof. Ikeda taught the 2nd half of MCB 300. He was a good lecturer that complemented Prof. Salyers well. Exams were easier than Prof. Salyers  but his material was in my opinion more interesting than Prof. Saylers'. Overall a nice guy who is apparently very helpful if you visit his office hours (or so I hear, I never went myself).
He's very clear, kinda funny, very helpful.  His exams are fair, but you still need to memorize everything.
He's a nice man - pretty clear during lecture...his tests are fair too, but really need to study...especially for his final which was pretty tricky.
